{"body": "Hm, interesting. IMO the result of running this at the console:\n\n    group.users.where(:foo => true)\n\nshould definitely be:\n\n    [#<User id: 1>]\n\nThat being said, when things are \"getting personal\" with AR, the ability to inspect those relations would be really useful.\n\n**Ideal case**\n\nI think the ideal case would be to have the console call some third method which wraps inspect in most cases and to_a in the case of a relation.\n\n**Shortest path**\n\nAlias \"real\" inspect on a relation to some other name so you can still call it.\n\nEdit: I know what relations are I promise", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/6585825", "created_at": "2012-06-26T19:45:07Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/6869#issuecomment-6585825", "updated_at": "2012-06-26T19:52:24Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 6869, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/agraves/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/agraves/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/agraves/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/agraves", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/agraves/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/agraves", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/agraves/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/55a209de4a0b6216ef22c1be40295b3a?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fe1bc55fb92b356f04a9885d51edd0fa2.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/agraves/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/agraves/received_events", "gravatar_id": "55a209de4a0b6216ef22c1be40295b3a", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/agraves/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "agraves", "type": "User", "id": 46964, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/agraves/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "5238027dbd3543c15100c2f8"}, "id": 6585825, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/r